## Secret Patterns (recommended for hooks)

The patterns below are a starting set for the optional Claude PreToolUse hook
that blocks `Write`/`Edit` when a likely secret would be written into a file.
Tune to your stack — false positives are worse than no hook at all. See the
`Hooks (Claude-only)` section in `AGENTS.md` for the hook config shape.

| Name | Regex | Why |
|---|---|---|
| AWS access key id | `AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}` | AWS access key prefix is publicly fixed. |
| AWS secret access key | `(?i)aws(.{0,20})?(secret|access)?(.{0,20})?[\"']?[A-Za-z0-9/+=]{40}[\"']?` | 40-char base64 secret near "aws". |
| GitHub PAT (classic) | `ghp_[A-Za-z0-9]{36}` | GitHub personal access token prefix. |
| GitHub fine-grained PAT | `github_pat_[A-Za-z0-9_]{82}` | Fine-grained PAT prefix. |
| Slack token | `xox[abprs]-[A-Za-z0-9-]{10,}` | Slack bot/user/app tokens. |
| Google API key | `AIza[0-9A-Za-z_-]{35}` | Google API key prefix. |
| OpenAI key | `sk-[A-Za-z0-9]{20,}` | OpenAI / Anthropic-style key prefix. |
| Generic private key block | `-----BEGIN [A-Z ]*PRIVATE KEY-----` | Catches RSA/OpenSSH/PGP private keys. |
| JWT-shaped token | `eyJ[A-Za-z0-9_-]{10,}\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{10,}\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{10,}` | Three base64 segments separated by dots. |
